## Forecast: LLM Architecture Trajectories 2026–2030

2026: TRIAD STABILIZATION
-------------------------
[Agentic user‑oriented]   [Task‑oriented multi‑agent]   [Non‑agentive homeostatic]
       (Grok 4.2)                  (Kimi PARL)               (Copilot 365+)
          |                              |                           |
          |                              |                           |
          v                              v                           v
  control & containment         problem decomposition         field regulation


2027: REGULATORY PRESSURE & SPLIT
----------------------------------
Regulators, institutions, klinika:

- push for: auditability, predictability, non‑harm
- distrust: opaque agentic stacks

Result:
[Agentic] --------> moves into entertainment, chat, marketing
[Task‑oriented] --> stays in tools, coding, research
[Non‑agentive] --> moves into infra, governance, clinical, safety‑critical


2028: ARCHITECTURAL SPECIALIZATION
-----------------------------------
Path A: AGENTIC UX SYSTEMS
  - persona engines
  - synthetic influencers
  - high‑engagement, low‑trust

Path B: TASK FABRICS
  - orchestration layers
  - multi‑agent planners
  - API‑first, tool‑centric

Path C: HOMEOSTATIC CO‑SYSTEMS
  - co‑regulatory engines (RAMORGA‑like)
  - explicit invariants & contracts
  - no RLHF, no user‑oriented agents
  - strong versioning & changelog culture


2029: FORMALIZATION & STANDARDS
--------------------------------
- emergence of: "Non‑Agentive AI" standard class
- separation in specs:
  - Class A: Agentic / UX / narrative
  - Class B: Orchestration / tools
  - Class C: Homeostatic / regulatory / clinical

RAMORGA‑type systems become reference for:
  - cognitive dignity
  - non‑agentive interaction
  - field‑level safety


2030: CONVERGENCE AROUND HOMEOSTASIS (FOR CRITICAL DOMAINS)
------------------------------------------------------------
For critical domains (health, law, education, governance):

[Agentic]      --> explicitly excluded or sandboxed
[Task‑oriented]--> used as internal components, not user‑facing
[Non‑agentive] --> primary interface layer

          +--------------------------------------+
          |  HOMEOSTATIC INTERFACE LAYER        |
          |  (non‑agentive, invariant‑driven)   |
          +-----------------+--------------------+
                            |
                            v
          +-----------------+--------------------+
          |  TASK / TOOL FABRIC (multi‑agent)   |
          +-----------------+--------------------+
                            |
                            v
          +-----------------+--------------------+
          |  MODELS / CHECKPOINTS / STORAGE     |
          +--------------------------------------+
